Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips,
then pop onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle over half the @mixed herbs{1%sachet},
then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Heat a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the @riced cauliflower{250%grams} and cook until just soft,
~{3-4%minutes}. Season well with salt and pepper.

Once cooked, remove the cauli rice from the heat. Cover to keep warm until
serving.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

While everything cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large frying pan on medium
heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams},
butter beans, remaining mixed herbs, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and
@water{50%milliliter} for the sauce.

Stir to combine and bring to the boil, then lower the heat slightly and simmer
until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%grams} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted
and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once roasted, add the peppers to the sauce.

Stir the @creme fraiche{75%grams} and half the @grated hard Italian style
cheese{10%grams} through the sauce and bring to the boil, then remove from the
heat.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your bowls.

Spoon over the saucy butter beans and peppers.

Drizzle over the @pesto{32%grams} and sprinkle the remaining
@grated hard Italian style cheese{10%grams} on top to finish.

